DOCS.GOOGLE.COM
Summer Band Lessons

Fulda High School Band & Choir
May 22 at 9:18 AM ·

Important FHS Band updates!:

First, there will be NO marching band this summer 😔 Our first three scheduled parades are cancelled, and the others are surely just waiting to announce cancellation until the last minute. Large group practices are also not feasible yet.

Second, there WILL be summer band lessons, upon request! 😁 To schedule lessons for your band student, either fill out the form attached below, or contact Mr. Saxman at 507-425-2514 ext. 3522 or matthew.saxman@isd505.org. As always, all band lessons are totally free. We have an administration-approved plan in place for practicing social distancing in the band room while learning to play instruments. Please ask if you have any concerns - safety is our #1 priority!

Last, "instrument try-outs" and first lessons for students exiting 4th grade/entering 5th grade will take place either in the fall, or as soon as more hands-on learning in school is possible. I will talk to the classes and contact parents when the time comes. 👍

Thanks for a GREAT year in band at Fulda Public Schools!

Good evening school families. While as a district we are waiting on more definitive information from the Minnesota Department of Education, we can provide some basic information to all of you. Starting Monday, March 30th distance learning will start for our students and run at least until April 30th. Parents, please check your emails tomorrow for more detailed information regarding distance learning. We will still continue to offer childcare for children of essential workers as well as offer meals for our students up to age 18. Please contact the school office is you are in need of meals or childcare beginning next week.

Thank you,

Loy Woelber, Superintendent of Westbrook Walnut Grove #2898, Fulda #505 and Lake Benton #404

post_text:
Firearms Safety Course 2020
This course is available to boys & girls. This course involves safe gun handling, care of firearms, live firing, hunting ethics, and wildlife management. This course is open to all persons who will be at least 11 years old on the by the first day of class. Successfully completing the class will earn the student a MN DNR Firearm Safety Certificate.
Dates: Saturdays – If no class due to weather, you will get a call from one of the instructors.
**Feb 29th , March 7th, 14th, 21st, 28th, April 4th
Time: 9:00-11:00 am
Location: Fulda Ambulance Hall – 305 E. Front St, Fulda
Cost: $7.50 PAYABLE TO: FULDA FISH & GAME
**DO NOT PRE-PAY, YOU WILL PAY DAY 1 OF CLASS
**After successfully completing the class, student and parent will need to log onto the DNR website to self-certify, pay the DNR $7.50 and then print their certificate.
April 18th is the field day. The bus will leave from the Ambulance Hall @ 1 p.m. sharp and return @ 5 p.m. In case of weather, it will be moved to the following Saturday.

post_text:
Cinderella's Closet:
All Girls from Fulda and MCC High Schools who are attending prom are invited to attend the Cinderella's Closet prom dress event sponsored by Hearts & Hands of Murray County!

This event will take place on Saturday, February 22 from 9:00am-12:00pm at Christ Lutheran Church in Slayton. Gently used prom dresses, shoes and jewelry will be available for FREE!

If you plan on attending, please email nikkicheskie@yahoo.com and give an approximate dress size. This will help us to plan ahead and do our best to have a variety of dresses in your size range.

If you have a dress, shoes or jewelry that you would like to donate, please contact Nikki Cheskie to arrange for drop off. All donations are tax-deductible!
